4. Impact on Economy: Analyze the money movement by e-commerce by looking 
at order prices, freight, and others. 
Get % increase in cost of orders from 2017 to 2018 (include months between 
Jan to Aug only) - You can use “payment_value” column in payments table. 
  Query: 
              with a as ( 
              select extract(year from o.order_purchase_timestamp) AS yr, sum(p.payment_value) AS cost
              _orders 
              from `case_study.orders` AS o 
              JOIN `case_study.payments` AS p 
              ON o.order_id = p.order_id 
              where extract(month from o.order_purchase_timestamp) between 1 and 8 
              Group by 1) 
 
            select round(((a1.cost_orders/a2.cost_orders)-1)*100,2) AS perc_increase 
            from a as a1, a as a2 
            where a1.yr = 2018 and a2.yr = 2017 

Observation: - 
• In this above query shows percentage increase in cost of orders from 2017 to 2018. 
• So, the result is 136.98% increase from 2017 to 2018. 
Recommendations: - 
• To see this I see the orders and payments table orders increase year by year. 
. 
 
